history.text: What is the name of the movie?
Jaws.
what is the movie about?

And it is a 1975 thriller directed by Steven Spielberg about a giant man eating great w
hite shark
is it a scary movie?
It is a scary thriller based in a New England SUmmer townd.
*town
what else can you tell me about the movie? would you recommend it?
I think I would.  It was directed by Spielberg, and has Richard Dreyfuss in it, so if you like them, then you'd likely like the movie.
does it have any other well known people in it?
With it being an older movie, I'm not sure you'd recognize the names, but it has Roy Scheider, Robert Shaw, and Lorraine Gray.
would it be okay for teenagers or kids to watch?

It starts with a beach party taking place on the island where a woman decides to go skinny dipping and gets violently pulled under.  If you're into them type of movies (and even if you're not) you'd likely enjoy it.  Spielberg is famous for a reason.
I would not advise children watching it, but older teenagers should be fine.
what is the movie rated?
I'm not sure what the rating is, but I would think it to be PG-13
The mayor tries to somewhat cover up this monster shark, because of fear it'll lose tourists.
what else can you tell me about the movie?
They initially catch a large tiger shark, and think that the beach is safe again.  They find a very large great white tooth afterwards, convincing the oceonagrapher that the shark is still there.
is this movie a musical? is it known for its songs or soundtrack?
By what I'm reading, I would think it's quite far off from a musical, and I don't think there is any noteworthy music in it.
It's a kind of dark thriller.
where did you say the setting of this movie is?
It is of a New England Island called Amity Island (unsure if that's a real island or made up for the movie however).
what else do you know about this movie?
the 3 main characters set out together to hunt the shark.
is it funny even though it is a thriller?
do they end up catching the shark?
I would say there is little to no humor involved.  They attempt to catch it, and it ends up sinking the ship the 3 guys are on.
is this one of steven speiburgs best films?
They stuff a pressurized scuba tank into it's mouth and blow it up.
It's certainly rated as though it would be one of his best.
